Kadane's Algorithm — Complete Explanation

Kadane's Algorithm finds the maximum sum of a contiguous subarray in O(n) time.

Problem

Given:

[-2, 1, -3, 4, -1, 2, 1, -5, 4]

Find the contiguous subarray with the largest sum.

Answer:

[4, -1, 2, 1]
Sum = 6

Core Idea of Kadane

Suppose we're at index i.

We have two choices:

Option 1

Start a new subarray from current element.

current = arr[i]
Option 2

Extend previous subarray.

current = previousSum + arr[i]

Take the better one:

currentSum = Math.max(arr[i], currentSum + arr[i]);

public class Kadane {

    public static int maxSubArray(int[] nums) {

        int currentSum = nums[0];
        int maxSum = nums[0];

        for(int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) {

            currentSum = Math.max(nums[i],
                                  currentSum + nums[i]);

            maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, currentSum);
        }

        return maxSum;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int[] nums = {-2,1,-3,4,-1,2,1,-5,4};

        System.out.println(maxSubArray(nums));
    }
}